node.text:
First you MUST stop thinking of them like recipes 
You are limiting yourself drastically by doing so 
There are #methods imbedded in recipes but you don’t make the connection when you read them, unless you are already a master of technique 
So you don’t learn anything, you don’t think to apply the same technique on something else because it’s not explained in detail enough for you to fly solo with it 
Let’s not kid ourselves, most chefs don’t write recipes and publish picture cookbooks to teach you how to cook, it’s more of a novelty, they write them to promote their restaurants or TV shows, that also, sadly, don’t really teach us how to cook 
My goal is for you to unfollow me in 1 year because you got mad technique and don’t need me anymore, that’s my home run here, and hopefully, in a perfect world, I will have your patronage at my restaurants because of my transparency 
Touch and feel with heat and the physical world is what you unlock when you teach technique 
You only need dream of what else you can perform magic on with heat and fat, while you watch the whites crisp up on the #crispyegg, to feel the power of possibility 
Or think of what else can be roasted until deeply concentrated and texturally complex like the #candiedyam 
Or what other veg can I sub for zucchini in the #PapaZukeMethod to fly around the house on your own 
These are lifelong skills that will never let you down, and they will stoke so much creativity from within you, that your spouses and family will literally blush at your artistic transformation 
Confidence, in any artistic endeavor is about mastering technique
It’s about practicing the basics in a wide forum until you start to feel your own voice within them 
I continue to break down every move I make in the kitchen, in detail, day after day, in a way everyone can grasp
So when you ask me for a recipe, I can’t help but laugh out loud, because I’ve already given you the keys to the kingdom of food in my highlights, but many of you just haven’t realized it yet 
#TeachYouToFish #FeedYouForLife #TechniqueIsEverything #WriteDownAndShareMethods #ThouShaltNotMeasure #JustFlow #FeelYourFood #FondleYourVegetables #SmellEVERYTHING

Next week is @CacioLovesPepe week @FrankRestaurant @LilFrankies @SupperNYC 
$11.95 Spaghetti Cacio e Pepe all week 
Happy 5th Birthday Cacio 
You are 35 in dog years 
I remember the first day I saw you at the pet store in Queens 
With that Lil white patch on your head and your glowing eyes 
We knew you were going to be our daughter the first time you wagged your butt and then laid down and gave up your belly, then your big long spinal stretch while we rubbed it with a long yawn just sealed the deal 
If you were here with me now you would be pushing away my iPad as I write this and insisting I rub your ears instead while Pepe sneaks up behind you and humps your butt
No I can’t play with you right now my darling, because I’m thinking of all the ways you have enriched my life 
From rolling around in my armpit scent to mask yours, to greeting me with such enthusiasm every time I return to the bedroom from the kitchen 
From holding my gaze for what’s seems like hours to barking at me to get out of bed and throw the ropey rope 
You are one helluva broad Cacio 
We always imagined you as our favorite diner waitress flashing your big butt and boobies while taking our orders, sly and charming, calm and self assured you charm the pants off all men 
#ShesTheCheese #CacioEpepe #MyMistressCacio #MansBestFriend #BeADogsBestFriend

node.text:
#AltoAdigeHarmony 
Cooperative, traditional, technical, simple 
Terroir, Terroir, #Terroir 
History. Majesty. 
I think of all these things 
I see even more things 
I see respect at its highest level 
Respect mostly for nature, but also for proven natural methods in the kitchen and at the wineries 
Less is so much more when you nurture nature 
Less ingredients, less manipulation, less waste, more flow
Michael at @manincor.wine has incorporated basic science to replace machines and taken biodiversity to a poetic level in all aspects of their wine making 
@gasser.klaus at @cantinaterlano tickles my butt when he uses spaghetti Pomodoro as an allegory for wine in Alto Adige 
He tells me people don’t realize how difficult the simple can be with his Pinot Bianco because its more about how do I take the incredible gifts of old vines, volcanic mineral rich soil, perfect climate with the protection of the mountains from the north and NOT just let that speak for itself?
How can perfect ripe tomatoes olive oil and basil not be enough?
What have I been beating into your heads about cooking and eating?
Nature is perfect as is, so the less we add and the more we flow TOGETHER with the natural tools she gives us, the better not only our creations will be, but also our lives will become 
#ItsReallyNotThatComplicated #WorkInHarmonyWithNature
#RestrainYourself #PutYourEarToTheGround #ListenToTheFlow #StareAtNature #LetItSinkIn #WeLiveInHeaven #RespectGodsGifts 
Watch my stories now on Merano, Otti at @miil.restaurant, @haller.alois at Forst, Terlano and Manincor and stay tuned for their more in-depth counterparts on 
YouTube.com/RealFrank to help you to grasp the simple and lead a richer more connected life

#ChasingGhostsAndAncestors on YouTube.com/RealFrank is about to start dropping with a Mozzarella factory in #Agerola and it will never stop 
The dedication to the #microregional food my ancestors protected 
Following in the footsteps of my ghosts 
Searching for the Mavericks of Italian cuisine and agriculture 
Sitting with the chefs and sommeliers who have absorbed history, and who respect tradition while pushing their regional pride forward 
The combined genius that’s makes #Italy the top destination for food and wine in the world non stop on both my social media platforms 
Thousands of wine varietals paired with all the foods they grow with 
The locations change but the quest for the simple historic and perfectly executed remains pure 
Nature, food, wine and song were designed to cure us, to ease us, to excite us and inspire us 
Discovery is the mantra 
Experience is the communication 
Love and respect shrouds everything
Today is my last day in Como
Merano and the region of Alto Adige is next with my son Vincenzo 
It’s time to be a dad again 
I can’t wait to see him 
#ItalianReinfection #FoodChoreographer #ExtremeHedonist 
#DesignTheBite #DeliciousAndNutritious

node.text:
Making #ChasingGhostsAndAncestors for my community puts me in a lot of restaurants and hotels in virtually every region of #Italy for three months out of every year flowing and searching 
I go from random inexpensive Hotels and Inns in not so well known towns in Piemonte, Abruzzo and Puglia to top hotels in Capri and Lake Como because I must constantly search for the best micro regional food experiences no matter where they lie, and in Italy they lie EVERYWHERE 
During that quest my own excitement often puts me in front of the actual people who protect and care for the micro regional Italy I kneel down to worship at the alter of
Like minded mom and pop operators of everything from wineries to restaurants 
Risotto rice farmers, fish distributors, truffle hunters, cheese producers, you name it
Kindred spirits who are often shocked at my pure passion for their home town methods and traditions, and at my trust of their recommendations in their Osterias and Trattorias 
Bonds are formed in those moments
Bonds that I know will grow into close friendships, as I help them reach more people with their genius through my social media presence 
You see I’m building an army of followers 
Who feel my passion 
To help me protect and promote the micro regional geniuses of Italy by featuring their dedication to craft in all aspects of my media, and even at home by recreating and teaching their dishes to the masses 
My next step will be to bring my YouTube.com/realfrank crew in to take a deeper dive with MY HANDS FREE to really get my points across to the camera lol 
It’s all coming 
#StayTuned #ItalianReinfection #ThisIsMyJob #FoodChoreographer

node.text:
The Resort Experience in Italy 
There are many hotels in Italy in such beautiful positions you really don’t want to leave them much 
The level of the service, food and warmth you get makes them incredible for unwinding because you are in good hands with nothing to worry about, or “much better to see” 
The hotels for #ChasingGhostsAndAncestors this summer are very special to me in that regard because I love to be isolated and forced to appreciate the simple beauty that is right in front of me all the time 
There is nothing better than connecting with an inspired restaurant everyday for lunch with a spectacular view, a simple menu and wine list, and a chef who is willing to venture beyond his own menu to make classics like spaghetti garlic and oil, and also other simple seasonal items, to make you see how you can have the same simple wonderful life back home
There’s always some nature to take in while you eat, it really doesn’t have to be this majestic, but sometimes it takes this kind of majesty to reset you into that frame of mind long enough to remember it, so you can summon it at will 
That to me is what a vacation is all about, and because I’m experiencing it now, it’s easy for me to conjure it even in a parking lot eating a sandwich looking at the sky over a strip mall 
Thats the purpose of this trip, to use music, the majesty of nature and its flavors on repeat, until it sinks in for me and all of you that everything simple about this earth is the entire ballgame no matter where you are 
A plate of pasta garlic and oil today is as good as it gets, or a simple Limone with the family and BOOM accept that you are happy 
If you are locked down or stressed, just cook and flow, play music and look at nature, it’s there, you’re there, now seize the day, and design the muthafukin bite 
#ItalianReinfection #ImRechargingForAllOfUs #PlugInToMe #ChangeYourPerspective #CookForOthers #PayWhatYouLearnForward #BeAVesselForLove 
This entire meal on the Veranda @villadestelakecomo is about to go up into my stories and my highlights

#HotelCaesarAugustus has impressed me yet again
It’s always the service that makes all the difference 
As you guys know I just go with the flow while making #ChasingGhostsAndAncestors and I am alone producing, shooting and editing this show on Instagram, so its really imperative I can count on the staff of the hotel to make my job easier by doing theirs flawlessly 
Having the support and advice of the #locals that run the #hotel is critical to me finding the hidden micro regional gems I’m always looking to learn from, and use as a pulpit, for the food I love to preach about, teach, eat, and serve to my clients
The hotel staff in many ways are production assistants 
The owner of @hotel_caesar_augustus Francesco has put together an amazing service #TEAM of truly warm, intelligent and genuine people
Vincenzo at the pool, Stefano at the bar and everyone in the dining room and at the front desk was there for each and every one of my needs instantly 
The maids were unbelievable, like magic everything was always clean and restocked making it so easy for me to concentrate on my work 
@francescadesanto_ you crushed it as concierge. You really understood what I was looking for. You delivered me to each restaurant doorstep you recommended whether by boat, taxi or foot flawlessly. The #Capri you showed me is truly the Capri I wanted to see.
I’m just so grateful for all of you honestly, you even laughed at all my jokes and sang along with me when I was feeling daffy 
17 days of true bliss 
#SoGrateful #ThisIsMyJob #WishICouldTakeYouAllWithMe #WhatAStaff #TopNotch #YouMakeMyJobSoEasy #KeepingMeSingingAndEating #ItalianReinfection

node.text:
Where do I eat in #Capri? 
Part Two: The Next Steps 
(See previous post for Part One)
So you trusted me, they crushed it and now you have a restaurant in #Italy where you know someone you trust to give you a great #regionalfoodexperience so whats next? 
Well you keep going back, you explore the rest of the #regionalmenu, you keep the conversation going and you get even more curious
You ask where they go to eat, and you get someone to ask for so you’re gathering even more like minded restaurant connections 
You see just by inserting yourself into the #microregional conversation you drop a gastronomic anchor into your favorite region of Italy that is eventually gonna need a bigger boat 
I trusted Pasquale @daGelsomina and he crushed it so I went back to hit the rest of the menu today with more questions and it just keeps getting better 
I see you have Puttanesca? Cozze con Limone? What is your relationship with these dishes? 
Who else makes it good? Is there any dissent on methods or ingredients? What did your mother do? 
And our relationship with food grows exponentially 
#WelcomeToTheRealItaly #Discovery #History #Cadence #EatLikeALocal #InsertYourself #StopAskingForPestoInPuglia 
#OrLasagnaInSicily 
#StayMicroRegional #GetWithTheProgram #ReapEnormousRewards 
I will be posting my second meal tonight at 6-8pm EST right here so stay tuned 
In order #RavioliCaprese, #SpaghettiPuttanesca, #CozzeLimone #ChasingGhostsAndAncestors

node.text:
Where do I eat in #Capri?
It’s not so much WHERE as it is WHAT do I order 
And this is true for all of Italy 
The first question is what kind of restaurant am I in? Is it a celebrated mom and pop regional gem?
Those are the best kind PERIOD, or someone’s home of course where you let them do the heavy lifting and you show trust and excitement and GRATITUDE
But let’s say it’s Capri and everything is expensive and you are scared to death of being taken advantage of as a tourist 
Well don’t be and listen up 
Have you done your research? Did you look up the food of #Campania and #Naples?
Order and inquire about those dishes even if you don’t see them on the menu and if you see something written in dialect immediately ask what it is 
PRIDE is every Italian restauranteurs weakness so if you don’t know the things on the menu that they would be proud of, you are already at a disadvantage in any major tourist area 
And if you don’t see anything regional or simple that you know you ask for the basics even if it’s not on the menu, like #SpaghettiPomodoro and #AglioeOlio or #SpaghettiVongole #InsalataCaprese which EVERY Italian is proud of and happy to make 
In sea areas you ask for a whole fish which tickles everyone pink, or grilled crustaceans and steamed mollusks 
Or simple pastas like #Paccheri or any handmade “spaghetti” with seafood 
You can also just ask, “what is the simplest best thing on the menu, that you are the proudest to make for us” 
Lay that shit down on the table, be aggressive in your quest to FIND the real Italy 
You will be surprised at the incredible experiences that sentiment will inspire 
Be prepared to be invited into Italian homes after you kick that door open because all I, or any Italian need see, is RESPECT and curiosity for the Italian micro regional kitchen before we become life long friends in food
#ItaliansLoveToShare #ItsHowWeAre #WeWantYouToSeeWhatWeSee #TasteWhatWeTaste #LoveWhatWeLove #WeWantYouToUnderstandWhy #WeRuleFood #ShowRespect #FeelOurPassion #WeNeedToShareIt #ItsinOurDNA #KickThatDoorOpenWithHumility #WeWillNeverShutItOnYou 
Please watch my highlights on Capri now where you will see in much more detail how I navigate it

Wake to #wakes in your #CapriWake
Everything leaves its mark 
What you gonna #wake?
Disturb the #sea 
Mess up some air 
Make waves 
Hit the throttle 
Bat your wings 
Flap your lashes 
Yell into the breeze 
Make snow angels 
Fornicate in a lake 
Shake some dice 
It all leaves a wake
Your wake 
Together with my wake 
And his wake 
And her wake 
Is our wake 
You can read the wake we shake 
The love we make 
The fate we take 
#LeaveYourWake 
#MakeYourselfKnown 
#LeaveItBetterThanYouFoundIt
#StartHereInCapri 
#LoveIsTheUltimateWake 
#WieldIt #WakePoem

node.text:
And so it begins again…
This time in Capri where your breath is taken from you with every twist of your neck 
Where the genuine excitement for life is so rampant and outrageous, you can’t help but to become fully contagious 
Starry eyed and enflamed you walk with an extra jump in your step 
Every time your foot steps forward your heart skips two beats 
And you truly can’t seem to take it all in 
Smiles are everywhere so you absorb them and put two on 
Faith in humanity is repeatedly restored for use again and again
You leave Capri but Capri never leaves you 
This fantasy Island is all anyone could ever need to give in to the majesty of nature 
The daily sunrises and sunsets are quite simply pure soul food 
Eat a true #InsalataCaprese with pure #BufalaMilkMozzarella and the local #BeefsteakTomatoes while watching either and you will immediately know why you were born 
There is nothing to compare #Capri to but Capri and I will be doing exactly that for the next 16 days here 
For the next two months I will be in Italy recovering and recharging and promoting the pure magic of micro regional Italy 
As a pure blood Italian I feel it is my duty to do so now more than ever 
I am also rewarding myself grandly and extravagantly for all the work I have done keeping my world in one piece this past year and I’m hoping that these fantastical  landscapes and meals coupled with an unbridled joy for life will help all of you to recover and/or continue fighting this crazy pandemic wherever you may be
#StayTuned #ChasingGhostsAndAncestors #ItalianReinfection #Summer2021 
#CapriFirst #ThenLakeComo #ThenAltoAdige #ThenPositano #ThenAmalfi

node.text:
23 years ago TODAY on #FathersDay in 1998 I opened my first restaurant #Frank 
I didn’t plan it that way, it just so happened I was ready on that day and it felt right 
My Dad lent me all the money and was there the whole day helping me get ready 
You see I’m one of the very lucky ones who had a father who believed in me 
But would never just give me money for whatever I wanted so it was hard for me to ask for it 
He made me earn everything and pay back everything he gave me and this would be no different, and the weight of that was all the motivation I needed 
You see all my childhood I had the deepest respect for my father and disappointing him was one of my biggest fears 
He did everything for us and I felt I could never take it for granted 
Thankfully @FrankRestaurant was a huge hit from day one, and on Christmas Day 6 months later I put a shoebox full of cash under his Christmas Tree with his entire investment packed into it 
A year or so later I made him retire early and come work for me as my Bookeeper which he continues to do for me to this day 
#HappyFathersDayDaddy #ILoveYou #IAmALuckyMan 
@bigciccio36 #HappyAnniversaryFrankRestaurant

node.text:
#SundaySermon 
#ForFathersDay especially for my sons
My path is paving itself in front of me 
I no longer worry about the future nor do I harp on the past 
I’m feeling like the level of my pure contribution to community has created a positive energy field that guides and protects me 
I know my body is made of atoms and atoms are mostly air so it feels like I’m floating in a tractor beam of good will 
When I concentrate, I feel all the space in any room entering and leaving my body 
Nothing is empty, it’s all pure energy
There is electricity especially between my fingers and toes, in my eyes, so many nerve endings I can direct into food, people and even the ground 
My deep connection to my own gut and digestion has in turn deeply connected me with my own soul 
I have no fear because I feel in #harmony with humanity and all my surroundings 
I use gratefulness to summon my deepest emotions and it soothes me when I feel stress 
Everything I’ve been through has brought me closer to #enlightenment so I congratulate instead of blaming myself for it 
With fasting I can clear my mind through my gut almost instantly 
I know I am the only one that can stop me from achieving all my dreams and my own happiness is a simple decision I make in every moment of every day 
I know I have earned the trust to make others feel the same way and I will never abuse that power while I wield it 
And lastly, because money does not control any of my decisions, I feel a pure independence from the grotesqueness of greed and the obsession with material things, and instead I spend the money I make, from feeding my community, lavishly on experiences and artistic collaboration, then pass them on through social media for free spontaneously and organically 
#IAmExactlyWhereIAlwaysHopedToBe #IAmHumbledByWhatGodHasGivenMe #YesIAmPreachingThroughFood #PayingItForward #FoodProphecy #FoodPriest #HappyFathersDay #BeThePatriarchYourFamilyNeeds #ItAllStartsWithCooking #ItsAllConnectedToFlow
